    <body>
      <trans-unit id="10333" identifier="d9d5697fb82b951021d3e19c3939ffee">
        <source>Make a variable called “black cards total” and set its value to 0.</source>
        <target>crwdns10333:0crwdne10333:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10334" identifier="6c8f9648fcc2a6ec20ca7cb6cdc2b43c">
        <source>Make a string variable called “cards” and set its value to the input
entered by the end user.</source>
        <target>crwdns10334:0crwdne10334:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10335" identifier="1663a31eb38e855565cd083b8038c33d">
        <source>Check each letter of the string and if it’s ‘B’ add 1 to the
“black cards total”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10335:0crwdne10335:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10336" identifier="9bca5c21160ae5a70d4ff30f9e7fb5c5">
        <source>Display the “black cards total” as the output.</source>
        <target>crwdns10336:0crwdne10336:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10337" identifier="f33d46db20b024d4b72d2e7e3943f53d">
        <source>You can access a letter at the specified position in a string by using
the &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter (1) of [world]&lt;/code&gt; block under “Operators”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10337:0[world]crwdne10337:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10338" identifier="b3f38b5bce22059c78a7498b774ea904">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter (1) of [world] //w&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10338:0[world]crwdne10338:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10339" identifier="bd28009f81711ace41c397a428f1015c">
        <source>In this challenge you need to access all the letters in user’s input and
check to see if each of them is equal to B (black).</source>
        <target>crwdns10339:0crwdne10339:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10340" identifier="4c8b5356652b84eab1850e4166a0d5fa">
        <source>You can find how many letters a string has by using the
&lt;code&gt;scratch:length of [world]&lt;/code&gt; block unders “Operators”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10340:0[world]crwdne10340:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[4]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
